Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.62,0:01:49.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.62,0:01:52.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do for Norman's sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.04,0:01:54.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.92,0:01:56.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.92,0:01:59.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.55,0:02:01.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to give up and free myself of the pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.59,0:02:03.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.97,0:02:06.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will never, ever give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.43,0:02:08.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let Norman die in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.22,0:02:10.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.69,0:02:15.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we're always thinking\Nthe same thing in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.81,0:02:17.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's run away, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.27,0:02:18.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I came here to talk about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.40,0:02:21.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to talk to you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.53,0:02:26.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These past two months, we couldn't really talk\Nsince we were worried about Mom watching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.41,0:02:31.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I didn't want Mom\Nto figure out our true intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.75,0:02:33.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True intentions?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.04,0:02:35.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Mom is really cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.17,0:02:41.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we weren't doing anything,\NMom never stopped watching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.42,0:02:43.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we could use that against her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.80,0:02:48.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If she's watching me, I could keep\Nher eyes away from people other than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.43,0:02:50.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don and Gilda, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.06,0:02:53.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I left everything to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.64,0:02:56.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Training for the escape,\Nand all other preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.44,0:02:57.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How far along are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.02,0:02:59.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.48,0:03:02.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Supplies, food, and warm clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.48,0:03:04.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can escape anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.20,0:03:05.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.20,0:03:07.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, how will you run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.91,0:03:10.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I worked that out too. I have a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.78,0:03:14.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's run away tomorrow afternoon,\Nbefore you get shipped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.21,0:03:16.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. It's reckless to go out during the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.58,0:03:18.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The situation's different from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.50,0:03:21.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We should leave at night\Nwhen it's easier to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.21,0:03:22.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hear me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.63,0:03:23.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.22,0:03:29.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. There are two problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.30,0:03:31.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First, Mom's watchful eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.10,0:03:36.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's always watching us, and she's always\Nholding one of the younger ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.94,0:03:40.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She'll be doing that during the day,\Nand at night, the babies are in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.02,0:03:44.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In order to escape with everyone,\Nwe'll have to shake Mom off,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.40,0:03:46.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and separate her from the little ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.11,0:03:50.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then, past the wall is a cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.03,0:03:52.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't climb down from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.95,0:03:56.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we're escaping, it'll be through the bridge.\NBut there's only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.08,0:03:59.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there's security to begin with,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.21,0:04:02.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and once they find out there's been an escape,\Nthe guards will rush there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.50,0:04:05.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, it's near the headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.71,0:04:08.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those monsters should be everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.13,0:04:11.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:17.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think this is the best answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.90,0:04:23.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.11,0:04:26.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At night, we'll light the House on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.94,0:04:28.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to start a fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.40,0:04:29.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.57,0:04:34.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When Mom is distracted putting it out, we'll lead\Neveryone outside, saying it's an evacuation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.91,0:04:37.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we seal the door to the secret room,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.75,0:04:42.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom can't notify headquarters, and\Nheadquarters will think it's a fire, not an escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.50,0:04:46.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then security won't go towards the bridge.\NWe can escape through it then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.76,0:04:53.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a bonus, I also hid ten Molotovs\Nbehind some rocks in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.30,0:04:54.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Molotov bottles?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.47,0:04:56.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate\Nmy six years of preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.35,0:05:02.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Throw those Molotovs into the neighboring plants\Non the way to the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.65,0:05:06.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If all goes well, there'll be another fire\Nto make security even scarcer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.57,0:05:08.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's nighttime,\Nno one will be in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:10.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No one will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.82,0:05:17.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So instead of tomorrow,\Nlet's run away tonight, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.88,0:05:24.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do it, Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.55,0:05:27.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.71,0:05:31.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This place is the farthest distance away\Nfrom everyone's rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.55,0:05:33.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They can escape before the fires get to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.84,0:05:37.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They've trained to run in formation\Nthrough tag, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.64,0:05:39.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or is your leg still...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.68,0:05:40.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.31,0:05:43.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.27,0:05:47.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.94,0:05:50.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, Emma...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.03,0:05:55.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth,\NI'm still against the idea of taking everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:06:00.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Especially after hearing\Nthere's a cliff beyond those walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.29,0:06:03.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you do take some,\Nit should only be Don and Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.71,0:06:06.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should at least leave the babies behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.38,0:06:10.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For their sake, and for yours, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.38,0:06:17.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you won't listen even if I stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.10,0:06:20.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it's better than having you\Nstay behind and not escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.02,0:06:21.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I won't say anything more.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.85,0:06:24.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.78,0:06:33.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So what are you doing?\NGo tell Don and Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.36,0:06:34.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You said...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.62,0:06:39.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to throw over the Molotov bottles?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.49,0:06:43.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You, or maybe Don could...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:52.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm worried about one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.88,0:06:57.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we start a fire,\Nwhat if Mom abandons the building?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.14,0:07:02.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She might give up on putting out the fire and\Nrefuse to take her eyes off of us, the merchandise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.81,0:07:04.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You realized, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.89,0:07:07.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's a good possibility of that happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.90,0:07:10.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why starting a fire won't be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.07,0:07:15.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't stop Mom, then we won't have\Nany chances of escaping from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.07,0:07:17.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.49,0:07:20.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just have to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.05,0:07:32.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.72,0:07:39.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this the greatest?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.55,0:07:42.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The perfect scorer\Nwith the set shipment date will burn up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.26,0:07:43.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She won't be able to abandon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.43,0:07:47.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.98,0:07:52.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I decided this a long time ago.\NMany, many years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.19,0:07:54.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a childish retaliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.20,0:07:57.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know what, Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.82,0:08:01.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've never really been interested\Nin studying or reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.74,0:08:08.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I endured it, and I worked hard\Nto improve my value to the highest it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:11.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Twelve years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.38,0:08:14.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a feast that they've been waiting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.67,0:08:16.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to take that away from them tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.88,0:08:18.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right before the harvest\Nthey've been looking forward to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.22,0:08:22.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think you can eat me.\NDon't think you can serve me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.76,0:08:25.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Food? Merchandise? I don't give a crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.72,0:08:28.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a human being! Serves them right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:30.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.35,0:08:32.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, it's fine this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.52,0:08:34.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the best way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.48,0:08:38.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've watched my family die all these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.61,0:08:40.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I used them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:43.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And they were all good kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.24,0:08:46.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They were kindhearted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.95,0:08:48.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Wait.\N- Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.46,0:08:52.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Emma. You only have one chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.96,0:08:54.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Make this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.42,0:08:58.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't let me, or Norman, die in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.43,0:09:04.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.64,0:09:11.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.63,0:09:39.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm now 12 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.63,0:09:44.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was a life I wanted to curse, but the time\NI spent with everyone was really fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.01,0:09:45.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.05,0:09:46.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.77,0:09:49.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-bye, Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.88,0:11:01.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Happy birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.38,0:11:03.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.09,0:11:05.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.77,0:11:17.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is this smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.03,0:11:25.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.20,0:11:28.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.45,0:11:33.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray! Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.08,0:11:36.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.13,0:11:39.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.04,0:11:41.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, help! Ray is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.46,0:11:42.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray is in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:55.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did he set himself on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.19,0:12:00.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.90,0:12:04.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gilda, take everyone outside!\NAlso please get the babies in my room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.74,0:12:05.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.12,0:12:16.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.66,0:12:18.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,at least get his brain...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.00,0:12:20.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.05,0:12:23.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.85,0:12:33.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't the sprinklers working?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.72,0:12:36.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, you need to get out of here too.\NOr else, you'll also...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.65,0:12:41.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.66,0:12:51.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.82,0:13:33.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What were those children...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.70,0:13:35.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,wearing on their feet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.83,0:13:44.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.75,0:13:46.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.30,0:13:54.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.02,0:14:03.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thank you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.56,0:14:05.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Bye-bye, Emma.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.12,0:14:20.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nice catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.25,0:14:20.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.96,0:14:24.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I'm not going to let you die.\NNot me, nor the other children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.83,0:14:26.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The other children?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.09,0:14:33.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I brought what you asked for, Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.43,0:14:35.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And everyone's already good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.18,0:14:38.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Thoma and Lanni.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.02,0:14:43.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Ray. Get changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.73,0:14:50.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Done changing? Then next is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.73,0:14:52.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.24,0:14:55.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.62,0:15:00.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still want to die, you blockhead?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.74,0:15:02.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop yapping because we're escaping!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:04.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, we're done here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.01,0:15:11.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.80,0:15:12.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your replacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.97,0:15:14.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It'll create a certain smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.64,0:15:17.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those braids...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.76,0:15:18.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anna gave them to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.97,0:15:21.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lastly, the tracking device.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.85,0:15:24.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take it out, so sit with your ear toward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.19,0:15:27.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.44,0:15:30.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"You can die anywhere,\Nand it doesn't have to be here."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.73,0:15:33.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll show you something cool,\Nso shut up and come."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.86,0:15:35.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A message from Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.70,0:15:38.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Norman?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.37,0:15:40.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To my dearest Emma...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.83,0:15:43.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm going to write down the plan from here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.37,0:15:46.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ray is planning to die.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.63,0:15:51.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's doing all this so you and I don't get killed.\NThat's what he said.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.34,0:15:54.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He didn't include himself in the equation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.63,0:15:56.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He has no intention of escaping.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.80,0:15:59.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He plans on dying inside this House.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.68,0:16:05.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's going to set himself on fire to distract Mom,\Nand let us run away.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.06,0:16:07.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's Ray's plan.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.73,0:16:10.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm not going to let him do that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.48,0:16:12.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.24,0:16:18.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's why I'm writing down\Nthe plan I came up with.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.41,0:16:26.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It'll happen in two months.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.58,0:16:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Probably the night before Ray's birthday.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.29,0:16:37.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Use the fire that Ray's planning to start,\Nsave Ray, outwit Mom, and escape with everyone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.51,0:16:41.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't worry. There's time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.01,0:16:44.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I also got an unexpected item.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.60,0:16:47.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was from Sister Krone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.24,0:17:00.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm counting on you, Emma.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.28,0:17:05.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please take care of Ray and our siblings.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.83,0:17:07.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And everything else.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.97,0:17:21.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's begin, Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.73,0:17:38.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.12,0:17:48.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay everyone, let's escape.\NWe'll run to the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.63,0:17:53.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.85,0:18:09.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Don. What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.35,0:18:14.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do they all know\Nabout the House and the escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.61,0:18:16.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Yup.\N- How?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.57,0:18:19.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma told them about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.57,0:18:22.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's tell more kids\Nother than Don and Gilda, Norman.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.66,0:18:30.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don, Gilda, and probably everyone else\Naren't as immature as we think.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.50,0:18:32.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we're going to run from those monsters,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.50,0:18:36.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I think it's better they know about the dangers,\Nand should willingly join our escape.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:42.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And Mom only suspects the oldest kids,\Nand not everyone else.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.01,0:18:45.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do you think it's reckless?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.59,0:18:46.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.60,0:18:49.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But with this plan,\Nwe can catch Mom off guard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.52,0:18:52.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Realistically, this is the only way\Nto escape with everyone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.85,0:18:56.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At first, we told four.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.40,0:19:00.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What do you want to know?\NGo ahead. Ask me anything.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.40,0:19:02.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Really, anything?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.15,0:19:06.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes. Whether it be about the farm\Nor about the headquarters...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.24,0:19:08.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.24,0:19:09.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}There are humans outside\Nwho haven't been eaten.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.66,0:19:09.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.83,0:19:13.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Then you don't know how long\Nthe demons have been around?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.16,0:19:12.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lannion. Thoma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.66,0:19:15.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We let them hear what Sister said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.00,0:19:17.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since that far back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.63,0:19:21.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the rest, we spent\Ntwo months slowly recruiting them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.09,0:19:24.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom probably didn't notice at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:30.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That Emma was only pretending to have given up,\Nbut was actually giving everyone instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:34.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Training for the escape,\Nand all other preparations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.23,0:19:35.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How far along are you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.64,0:19:36.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everything is ready.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.98,0:19:40.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Supplies, food, and warm clothing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.15,0:19:41.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We can escape anytime.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.45,0:19:49.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:03.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Norman.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.97,0:20:17.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nat and I will climb up first.\NThen we'll pull everyone up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.69,0:20:21.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, everyone! Just do it\Nlike how we trained, and you'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.27,0:20:23.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's going to escape safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.65,0:20:27.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.83,0:20:43.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's burning. Everything is burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.84,0:20:45.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:21:00.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're still alive! Emma and Ray, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.15,0:21:05.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you escape, my adorable children.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.11,0:21:10.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this all of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.79,0:21:16.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
